@jvgutierrez I have been investigating this issue and seems like there it is a problem when you use the `functools.wraps` or nothing in your decorators. The `functools.wraps` does not pass the information about parameters of the original function to the decorated instance. This makes connexion fail to get the argument list defined in the original function.

A solution I recommend is to use the [`decorator`](https://github.com/micheles/decorator) package since [pass the information](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3972290/how-can-i-get-the-argument-spec-on-a-decorated-function) about the defined argument list of the original function to the decorated instance.

I will update our example to use the `decorator` package and try to fit in our documentation an alert on that matter.

