@wisechengyi 
Addressed your most recent comments, but may need to discuss the `Exception` in buildozer. Here was my reply to your earlier comment:

>The caught exception is allowing the meta-rename task to rename dependencies in both the full <address.spec> and :<target_name> formats. I believe buildozer needs exact name/pattern matching. So to handle both formats there is this logic that first tries to rename <address.spec>, but if it fails, then tries :<target_name>. Perhaps there's a better way to figure out the dependency format in the BUILD file without doing a regex or string match.

